  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>ciabatta rolls</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 6-7 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into thin batons</p><p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>courgette batons</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until they have slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>parsley</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until they start to brown</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped parsley</strong>,<strong> </strong>crumble in <strong>half</strong> the <strong>feta</strong>, stir everything together and set aside – this is your <strong>gremolata</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>garlic paste</strong>, <strong>'nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>butter beans</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Crumble in 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>Knorr chicken stock cube</strong>,<strong> tomato paste </strong>and the <strong>juice</strong> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[280ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook covered for 1-2 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan, stir it through the sauce and cook for 30 sec or until it has started to wilt – this is your <strong>saucy 'nduja & beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-saucy-nduja-and-beans-with-gremolata/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges and tear the <strong>warmed ciabatta</strong> in half</p><p>Serve the <strong>saucy</strong> '<strong>nduja & beans </strong>with the<strong> warmed ciabatta </strong>to the side and top with the <strong>gremolata</strong></p><p>Crumble over the<strong> remaining feta </strong>and garnish with the<strong> lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
